article.headline: Suggs scores 17, including game-winner, as ECU tops Memphis

images.name: East Carolina wins on miraculous buzzer-beater
images.caption: Brandon Suggs drains the game winner off the inbounds pass with only 1.0 remaining, as East Carolina defeats Memphis 72-71.

article.linkText: Suggs scores 17, including game-winner, as ECU tops Memphis
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. -- — Vance Jackson and Brandon Suggs scored 17 points each and East Carolina defeated Memphis 72-71 on Saturday. Memphis led by 14 at halftime and still by 10 with 2:22 remaining in the game. East Carolina scored 10 points to tie it and after a Memphis free throw, Suggs buried a jumper for the win with 2 seconds left. Alanzo Frink, Tremont Robinson-White and Tristen Newton added 11 points each for the Pirates (11-5, 2-2 American). Jalen Duren had 15 points and nine rebounds to lead five in double figures for Memphis (9-7, 3-3). —-
